race.comment: NOW SHOWING (2) got a long way back over this course and distance last time out and ran over the top to score in impressive fashion. He may be able to sit a touch closer from a better gate this time around and if he can replicate the way he finished off last start, he can get the job done again. CALEB (3) is another who flew home to win, scoring by a nose over the 1400m trip. The form out of that race has been good and he possesses plenty of upside going to the mile now. May get back in the run, but watch for his finishing burst. TRULY SUPREME (7) couldn't reel in the winner here a fortnight ago, beaten 0.2L at this track and trip. The inside draw is a big tick and he sat on the speed last time he drew and inside barrier. Expecting another forward run today. CRAMPIN' MY STYLE (4) is ticking along nicely this time in work and can't be discounted. HOT NOVA (12) was best of the rest behind a dominant winner in town last week and has to be included.
